Trauma to elbows, knees, and ankles.
 In summary, the emergency department or office-based physician should distinguish first between inflammation and injury.
 A clinical diagnosis of fracture should be made before obtaining and reading films.
 Comparison views help to resolve doubt.
 A neurologic examination should be documented before undertaking reduction.
 Finally, if in doubt, a splint for 24 to 48 hours until an orthopedic opinion is available causes no harm.
